File: The power utility is urging the public to use electricity sparingly this weekend. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has warned that load-shedding will resume on Sunday morning from 9am until 10pm. In a statement released on Saturday, the power utility says demand for electricity has risen. READ: Stage 2 load-shedding to resume "Implementing load shedding tomorrow is necessary in order to replenish the emergency generation reserves to better prepare for the coming week. Due to much colder weather, demand for electricity has also risen significantly," read the statement. The power utility is urging the public to use electricity sparingly this weekend.